       There are two general ways to specify a color when you are
       customizing your environment:

          +o Create a color directly using a hexadecimal number

          +o Use a predefined color name

       To specify a color directly, that is, without using a color
       name, use a three-part hexadecimal number.  The three parts
       of the number specify the intensity of red, green, and blue,
       respectively as shown in Figure A-1.

